<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/103273712-michelle-haggard"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/103273712-michelle-haggard">Michelle Haggard</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Book 2 is quite different from books 1 and 3. I almost did not proceed to book 3 because book 2 was not that interesting, only supplying two facts for<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Book 2 is quite different from books 1 and 3. I almost did not proceed to book 3 because book 2 was not that interesting, only supplying two facts for book 3. Book 3 was very good though. I think you are better off reading just books 1 and 3. Book 3 is complete enough in itself.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
