  <span id="freeText8744313857495609802" style="display:none">This book is 1/3 this:<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1519432125i/25112548._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>And 2/3 this:<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1519432125i/25112546.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Quite a fantastic and epic story! A casino caper and a swashbuckling adventure combining action, deception, romance, and humor - this book has it all. Very well written. Even with the length of the story, I never felt that it had gone on too long. Definitely no filler.<br><br>This is a sequel and I think I like it better than the first. That is saying a lot because the first was great! In this case, I will say something I don't usually say - I think you could read this one without reading the first and be just fine. While they do bring up some events from the first book, the author does a great job making this book it's own.<br><br>So, do you like epic awesomeness? Crossbow battles? Death by poison? Wild pirate sex? Baskets full of cats? Then look no further!<br><br>That's right, I said BASKETS FULL OF CATS!<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1519432125i/25112547._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
